						               													<description>From beyond the Grave is a Roll and Write, Print and Play Single Player adventure that plays in 15-30 minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The city of Nilam hides a grotesque secret that dates back to the construction of the Cathedral. On an ominous day in December 1819, someone broke the seal that prevented the souls of the slaughtered from pouring into the city. Since that day, corruption of the flesh, depravity and vengeance have run rampant in the streets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You wear the cloak of one of the Saviors, special members of the High Council, and your task is to unveil the mystery and put an end to the horrors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Choose one of four characters with special abilities. Then you take the first of three districts maps and start your quest. The story is divided into six chapters with three different tasks that you have to fulifill in order to advance. At the beginning of your turn, roll 2 dice. Pick one die and move of a number of spots up to the obtained result.&amp;#10;The unused die can be saved for later in your Character Card.&amp;#10;When you step on specific spots on the map, you can perform different actions, such as fight, heal, shop or discover mysteries that bring the story forward.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You win by completing all tasks and lose when you get killed by the Horrors or time runs out!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Save Nilam. Save its citizens. Save yourself from the curse.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
